From: Dynamo <dev@nvidia.com>
Subject: [PATCH] multimodal_gen: default all CPU offload knobs to False

Flip every `*_cpu_offload` default from `None` (auto-decide) to `False`,
and flip `pin_cpu_memory` from `True` to `False`. With the previous `None`
defaults the auto-decide logic in `_adjust_offload` /
`_adjust_platform_specific` enables offload on GPUs below the memory cutoff
or for Wan/MOVA pipelines. That auto-enable exposes latent-vs-generator
device-mismatch failures in the realtime path, since
`prepare_latents` reads `self.transformer.device` (CPU under offload) while
`RealtimeVideoGenerationsRequest.generator_device` defaults to "cuda".

Targets: antgroup/sglang `chunk_diffusion` (sgl-project/sglang#19817).

Applied at image build time from the Dynamo SGLang runtime Dockerfile
(`container/templates/sglang_runtime.Dockerfile`). Callers that still
want offload can opt in explicitly via `--dit-cpu-offload true` or
kwargs to `DiffGenerator.from_pretrained(...)`.

---
 python/sglang/multimodal_gen/runtime/server_args.py | 12 ++++++------
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/python/sglang/multimodal_gen/runtime/server_args.py b/python/sglang/multimodal_gen/runtime/server_args.py
--- a/python/sglang/multimodal_gen/runtime/server_args.py
+++ b/python/sglang/multimodal_gen/runtime/server_args.py
@@ -161,14 +161,14 @@
     lora_target_modules: list[str] | None = None

     # CPU offload parameters
-    dit_cpu_offload: bool | None = None
-    dit_layerwise_offload: bool | None = None
+    dit_cpu_offload: bool | None = False
+    dit_layerwise_offload: bool | None = False
     dit_offload_prefetch_size: float = 0.0
-    text_encoder_cpu_offload: bool | None = None
-    image_encoder_cpu_offload: bool | None = None
-    vae_cpu_offload: bool | None = None
+    text_encoder_cpu_offload: bool | None = False
+    image_encoder_cpu_offload: bool | None = False
+    vae_cpu_offload: bool | None = False
     use_fsdp_inference: bool = False
-    pin_cpu_memory: bool = True
+    pin_cpu_memory: bool = False

     # ComfyUI integration
     comfyui_mode: bool = False
